Hello people! I'm now starting a new semester. The Askr & Embla painting is pretty much done and it's already traveling to the city where the painting contest is being held. I feel like a mother that let her son go to a field trip with his classmates. My girlfriend, Iris, also submitted some nice work. Unfortunately I don't have pics to show you guys. Anyways I really hope it gets someone's attention ='( OK so moving on! This semester I'll oil paint some more Skateboards. I'll try to make them better than that other time... which was more of a practice thing. I'll make 6 of them. Nude female studies. I'll try and get some nice ladies in there so I can aim the product to the macho man market. and perhaps I could even end up selling some outside Peru, if you guys are interested. This time I'll use brand new skateboards and not used and broken ones. Why? well, because people used to ask me if they could ride on those... it would definitely break my heart but if they pay for those they can do whatever they want with them. but the only usage I make these for is just display. Alright let the hard work begin!

Sorry for the lack of updates I am currently finishing school works for my finals. Also my Intuos2 is officially broken and I'll be buying a brand new Intuos3 pretty soon. I was going to buy a Cintiq 12WX but I really thought a lot about it and asked lots of pros out there and they told me that I don't really NEED a Cintiq and that I would be better of with my intuos. each have their pros and cons but I think I'll just save $700 for now and maybe buy the new ATI 4870x2 Card when it releases w00t! Ati is smoking Nvidia so far at least in the cost-performance ratio and that new card is just going to be a BEAST. Also I bought a new domain name so pretty soon I'll gather some time to make a decent portfolio website again at least for my clients. It will be www.iamalexxx.com cheers! *I live in Peru and these events happened in a Macdonald's near the American Embassy*

so there I was sitting in a McDonald's restaurant waiting for a friend to finish her burger. I had my good old sketchbook with me so I said hey let's do some stealth drawing!!!*Yay* looking for a victim I found two big men in suits sitting in a table. They looked pretty cool because they had these elegant suits, so I decided to sketch them. My pace was pretty good I was almost finished with the bald guy and I just needed to add some final details of his face. As I look back for the final touches *LIGHTNING!* he realized what I was doing! and he really caught me off guard! I couldn't fake it and if I did I did it real bad. After that he came to me and said in bad Spanish that for my own safety I should stop making drawings of them. *I didn't wanted them to know I speak English so I spoke back in Spanish* I told them that it was cool; but still deep inside of me I was like 'shit wtf was that!?' He then went back to his sit with his partner. When that little shock ended I just started sketching some other people but I could still see them talking and looking back at me. After a little while they both came back near me and speaking in English his parter tells the other guy to tear off my page. I did it myself and gave it to him just to avoid some trouble. *sigh* OK I guessed they got what they wanted, but they were still acting kinda weird. I saw one of them making a phone call. A third dude enters the restaurant. This dude speak Spanish fluently and asked me to go with him for a second. I then found out that he was a anti-terrorist agent. and that these two other guys were US Government Officials. He told me they felt threatened if someone takes pics of them or just draw them. he then began to interrogate me like if I was some kinda of terrorist. I wished I WAS back then! freaking' paranoid people! THEY EVEN CALLED MY SCHOOL TO SEE THAT I WAS REALLY AN ART STUDENT!!!

after that I was free and walked near the US embassy, there was this cool tank parked in front of the main gate. I took out my sketchbook and began sketching!
AWFUL DAYS OF FINAL EXAMS!!! VIVA REDBULLS!
